## Exit criteria

- `make test` green; new tests pass.
- `make lint` green.
- Re-run on `tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris` after this lands: at
  least 5 of the previously-title-searched JOUR records flip to
  DOI-based lookups (the ones whose PDFs printed the DOI on page 1).
  Manual eyeball, not asserted.
- The provenance trail makes the source clear: a record fixed via
  PDF-first-page DOI extraction must have an N1 line ending
  `source=pdf-firstpage`.

## Out of scope

- Multi-page DOI scan. First page only — by far the highest-density
  location and matches ticket 0014's contract.
- DOI normalization (uppercase → lowercase, percent-decoding, etc.).
  Most DOIs come out clean; if normalization becomes painful,
  separate ticket.
- Conflict between extracted DOI and resolver-returned DOI. If the
  extracted DOI takes us to a different record, the resolver's
  cross-check (future ticket) is the right place to flag it. This
  ticket trusts the regex hit.
